    slug: `video-production-vs-written-content-global`,
    title: `Video Production vs Written Content: What Global Brands Should Prioritize`,
    date: '2024-11-30',
    category: 'Content',
    location: 'Global',
    readTime: '9 min',
    excerpt: `Both video production and written content can drive growth. But for most Global businesses, one should come first. Here is how to decide.`,
    content: `<p>One of the most common questions SA Media gets from Global business owners is whether to invest in video production or written content first. Both are legitimate growth levers. Both take time to compound. And most businesses do not have the budget to go all-in on both simultaneously. So how do you choose?</p>
<h2>What Video Production Does Best</h2>
<p>Video Production is strongest when you need emotional brand storytelling and high engagement rates. For Global businesses in early stages or with a specific near-term revenue target, video production often delivers faster, more measurable returns. The feedback loops are shorter and you can iterate quickly.</p>
<h2>What Written Content Does Best</h2>
<p>Written Content is strongest when you need scalable, measurable growth in your target market. It tends to build compounding value over time - the investment you make in written content in month one pays dividends in month twelve and beyond. For Global businesses with a longer horizon, it is often the smarter play.</p>
<h2>The SA Media Recommendation</h2>
<p>At SA Media, we rarely recommend choosing one over the other in isolation. Our integrated model means video production and written content reinforce each other. Your video production performance data informs your written content strategy and vice versa. This is how the global media firm model works in practice: everything is connected.</p>
<p>If you are a Global business trying to allocate a limited marketing budget, the most important conversation you can have is with a strategic partner who understands both channels. SA Media offers a free consultation for Global businesses ready to build a program that works.</p>`,
