    content: `<p>One of the most common questions SA Media gets from Toronto business owners is whether to invest in SEO or paid media first. Both are legitimate growth levers. Both take time to compound. And most businesses do not have the budget to go all-in on both simultaneously. So how do you choose?</p>
<h2>What SEO Does Best</h2>
<p>SEO is strongest when you need compounding organic traffic and long-term cost efficiency. For Toronto businesses in early stages or with a specific near-term revenue target, SEO often delivers faster, more measurable returns. The feedback loops are shorter and you can iterate quickly.</p>
<h2>What Paid Media Does Best</h2>
<p>Paid Media is strongest when you need immediate, measurable results and precise audience targeting. It tends to build compounding value over time - the investment you make in paid media in month one pays dividends in month twelve and beyond. For Toronto businesses with a longer horizon, it is often the smarter play.</p>
<h2>The SA Media Recommendation</h2>
<p>At SA Media, we rarely recommend choosing one over the other in isolation. Our integrated model means SEO and paid media reinforce each other. Your SEO performance data informs your paid media strategy and vice versa. This is how the global media firm model works in practice: everything is connected.</p>
<p>If you are a Toronto business trying to allocate a limited marketing budget, the most important conversation you can have is with a strategic partner who understands both channels. SA Media offers a free consultation for Toronto businesses ready to build a program that works.</p>`,
